BBC.Later.with.Jools.Holland.S45E02.1080i.h264-NX

BBC 2 HD 26th Sep 2014
11:05pm to 00:05am S45E02 Recorded

Joining Jools is New York's Mary J Blige who returns to the show for the fifth time to debut tracks from her forthcoming album The London Sessions. Another homage to London comes from Marianne Faithfull who performs songs from her album Give My Love to London. From Southampton, a Later debut for rock trio Band of Skulls with songs from their third album, Himalayan, and there is another debut for Irish singer-songwriter Hozier. Swedish sisters Klara and Johanna Soderberg aka First Aid Kit also debut on the show with songs from their second album, Stay Gold. Plus GoGo Penguin, a trio from Manchester whose second album v2.0 has been described as 'jazz meets electronica'. And joining Jools for a chat is actor, DJ and musical enthusiast Idris Elba, who talks about the album he's conceived and produced called Mi Mandela, exploring the music of South Africa he discovered whilst shooting The Long Walk to Freedom.
